==English==

===Etymology===
{{PIE root|en|deh₃}}
From {{der|en|LL.|additivus}}, from the participial stem of {{der|en|la|addere|t=to add}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈæ.dɪ.tɪv/|lang=en}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈæ.də.tɪv/|[ˈæ.ɾə.tɪv]|[ˈæ.ɾə.ɾɪv]|lang=en}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# {{lb|en|mathematics}} pertaining to [[addition]]; that can be, or has been, [[added]]
# {{lb|en|mathematics|of a [[function]], etc.}} [[distributive#English|distributive]] over [[addition]]
#: {{ux|en|Matrix multiplication is '''additive''' in that <math>M\vec v+M\vec w=M(\vec v+\vec w)</math>.}}
# {{lb|en|algebra}} having [[addition]] as an [[operator]]
#: {{ux|en|It is natural to look at a finite cyclic group as an '''additive''' group.}}
# {{lb|en|chemistry}} pertaining to chemical [[addition]]
# {{lb|en|genetics}} describing [[gene]]s (or the interaction etc. of such genes) which govern the same trait and whose effects work together on the [[phenotype]]

====Antonyms====
* {{l|en|subtractive}}

====Derived terms====
{{der3|additive color|additive function|additive group|additive identity|additive inverse|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[substance]] added to another substance or [[product]] for its ability to [[alter]] its [[properties]]
#: {{ux|en|Oil may be used as an '''additive''' in gasoline to improve the lubrication of a small engine.}}
# {{lb|en|grammar}} a [[word]] or [[phrase]] that adds something, such as ''also'', ''even'', or ''nor''

